(- Use for drafting, summarizing, checklists, and process guidance) Tj
T*
(- Keep human approval for external communication and high-risk decisions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2\) Customer-Facing Assistant) Tj
T*
(- Website/chat assistant for FAQs, booking, order status, and triage) Tj
T*
(- Escalate complex or sensitive cases to staff automatically) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3\) Executive Decision Support) Tj
T*
(- Weekly AI-generated briefings: sales trends, inventory risks, customer pain points) Tj
T*
(- Scenario modeling for pricing, staffing, and demand changes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Suggested 90-Day AI Adoption Plan) Tj
T*
(Phase 1 \(Weeks 1-2\): Discovery) Tj
T*
(- Pick 2-3 painful workflows with clear KPIs) Tj
T*
(- Confirm data sources and owners) Tj
T*
(- Define governance: privacy, access controls, approval steps) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Phase 2 \(Weeks 3-6\): Pilot) Tj
T*
(- Launch one internal copilot and one automation workflow) Tj
T*
(- Measure baseline vs pilot outcomes) Tj
T*
(- Train a small champion team \(operations + IT + front line\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Phase 3 \(Weeks 7-12\): Scale) Tj
T*
(- Expand only if KPI lift is proven) Tj
T*
(- Standardize prompts, review gates, and escalation rules) Tj
T*
(- Build a reusable ?AI playbook? for future departments) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Governance and Risk Controls \(Canada/Saskatchewan Context\)) Tj
T*
(- Treat personal/business-sensitive data as protected by default) Tj
T*
(- Apply least-privilege access to AI-connected systems) Tj
T*
(- Keep audit logs for prompts, outputs, and approvals) Tj
T*
(- Use human-in-the-loop review for legal, finance, HR, and public-facing outputs) Tj
T*
(- Align privacy handling with applicable Canadian law \(including PIPEDA in private-sector) Tj
T*
(commercial contexts\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Budget and ROI Guidance) Tj
T*
(- Start small: one assistant + one workflow automation) Tj
T*
(- Typical KPI targets for first 90 days:) Tj
T*
(  * 15-30% reduction in admin time on selected process) Tj
T*
(  * 10-20% faster cycle times on selected workflow) Tj
T*
(  * 5-15% reduction in avoidable rework/errors) Tj
T*
(- Reinvest savings into data quality and staff training before broad rollout) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Failure Modes to Avoid) Tj
T*
(- Buying tools before defining the workflow and KPI) Tj
T*
(- No owner for AI outputs and quality review) Tj
T*
(- Over-automating customer communications without escalation paths) Tj
T*
(- Ignoring staff enablement and change management) Tj
